1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with stopping sets and stopping set distributions of linear codes, which are important concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of determining stopping sets and stopping set distributions for algebraic geometry codes, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents algorithms for determining stopping sets and stopping set distributions of algebraic geometry codes, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the performance analysis of iterative decoding for linear codes, which is a topic of interest in systems and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the stopping distance of algebraic geometry codes, which is a measure of the error-correcting capability of the code and is relevant to cryptography and security.
